<reference id="api_setscreencapturecontenthint">
    <title><ph keyref="setScreenCaptureContentHint"/></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc">Sets the content hint for screen sharing.</ph></shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <metadata>
   <keywords>
       <indexterm keyref="setScreenCaptureContentHint" />
   </keywords>
        </metadata>
    </prolog>
    <refbody><section id="prototype">
        
        <p outputclass="codeblock" conref="../conref/conref_rtc_api.dita#apidef/setScreenCaptureContentHint"/>
        </section>
        <section id="detailed_desc">
   
   <dl outputclass="since">
       <dlentry>
  <dt>Since</dt>
  <dd>v2.4.0</dd>
       </dlentry>
   </dl>
   <p>A content hint suggests the type of the content being shared, so that the SDK applies different optimization algorithms to different types of content. If you don&apos;t call this method, the default content hint is <ph keyref="CONTENT_HINT_NONE"/>.</p>
   <note type="attention">You can call this method either before or after you start screen sharing.</note>
        </section>
        <section id="parameters"><title>Parameters</title>
   <parml>
       <plentry>
  <pt>contentHint</pt>
  <pd>The content hint for screen sharing. See <xref keyref="VIDEO_CONTENT_HINT"/>.</pd>
       </plentry>
   </parml>
        </section>
        <section id="return_values">
   <title>Returns</title>
   <ul>
       <li>0: Success.</li>
       <li>&lt; 0: Failure.</li>
   </ul>
        </section></refbody>
</reference>
